annotation.TEXT: Careful of the magnets here.
Okay, there was a clear hit with one of my shots, just to show that they don't explode.
Nuts! Okay, you know what? I'm just gonna restart. There's a spot near the end of this level that I'm pretty sure I'm going to take hits on, and I'll need some spare HP to survive those hits.
Ooh, but I got it perfectly this time! Huzzah! Okay, now I just have to clear the level!
Okay, let's now proceed with the level some more.
Now, the B gate here needs to be open to proceed, and the way to do that is down here.
And, that one died in four shots. That one was easier to deal with since I had a solid floor to make use of.

Even worse is if I accidentally grab the edge of the window and resize it, which actually happened during this session. I restarted the level it happened on (7-2), and edited out that barfed run so you guys wouldn't notice.

Sweetness! Not quite a full combo, because of the purple rotator button I had to stand on earlier, but still really good. (Maybe a full combo is possible if I deal with the purple button before killing the first two enemies...)
Now, remember those small red "!" dots in the previous level? Well, these moving dots are different, as they don't explode when shot or rammed, but they do still hurt if you touch them, so watch out.
Alright, so let's blast this sniper up here next, and then take the path below.

BTW, full comboing this level certainly is possible, since mana is definitely not an issue, but I imagine it would be a pain, mainly due to the red "!" challenge, along with hoping not to screw up elsewhere.
Okay, carefully go down this way to reach that gem. It's pretty straightforward, and gives you an opportunity to get more used to these magnets.
Man, this is not going very well.
Alright, time to end off with a Time Attack level as usual. I believe 3-4 is next, and I'm gonna go at it with Taser Daria.
Next, navigate through some tight laser corridors, being careful to properly compensate for the magnets' pulls as you go.
Alright, with the last gem collected, let's finish the level. Just gotta carefully dodge those moving red dots...
To be continued... Yo! (And, don't forget to vote!)
And that gimmick is... magnets!
...he was sitting on a gem! But, I accidentally went through the one-way wall again, so let's circle around a third time...
Okay, try to be very careful, because there are magnets pulling in all different directions here.
That sniper was destroyed with just 4 shots. I wonder why the first sniper was made to be tougher?
And, as you can see, being in a magnet's pull is sort of like being underwater, as your mana refills very quickly, essentially giving you unlimited mana while you're magnetized.

Okay, that run was far from perfect, but I don't feel like trying again right now. (Still better than my practice run with Daria beforehand, which scored only about 5100, but I then tried it again with Mira and got over 7100!)
Okay, carefully dodge the moving dots here, and then shoot the sniper on the right. Fortunately, the magnet is far enough away that the sniper won't shoot at you if you're hugging it.
C-C-C-C-COMBO BREAKER!!! (3 kills, 3000 points)

Next, as a little shortcut, you can nudge the block out of the way of the laser again and then go straight up this way. It's not required to do that, though, as you can just go back the way you came through the yellow gate as well.
Okay, is that good enough?
Simply move this metal box to allow the laser to hit the B node. However, if you want gem #2, make sure you send the box to the right, like this.

And there's still plenty of coins yet to come that Irvette can use to heal, such as the ones right next to the purple button. Oh, and speaking of those coins, don't they look sort of like an arrow pointing right?
The taser sounds quite different underwater. Fortunately, Daria isn't electrocuting herself, as the costumes don't affect actual gameplay at all.
Careful now...
Okay, carefully go to the right here, fighting against the magnets so you don't hit the lasers above, but also being careful not to crash into the lasers below.
Awesome combo! (8 kills, 18,000 points)
Whew, nice. Okay, now I want to try to completely dodge the next magnet if possible, since it's just bad news.
Okay, that unlocked two new levels. First, there's 7-A, which requires 11 red gems, since it's a W7 blue level.
Pfft... Whatever. At least I wasn't in the middle of a combo.
Well, that's a very subtle hint to a stumper of a puzzle coming up. Now, normally, you'd rotate this purple door to the left so you can get through. But, rotate to the right a bit first.
Nice. Now, carefully go to the left to deal with another sniper and hit the yellow gate switch...
Now, I usually get hit while going for this gem...
Yeah, just like that.
ERGH!!! Sometimes it takes a bit of effort to break free from a magnet's grasp. Try not to lose control while doing so.
You guys didn't forget about voting, did you? Anyway, let's take Robin Hood Irvette into this level, which features a new gimmick.
Yep, they do what you expect, and pull you in. I guess something I'm wearing is magnetic. However, you can certainly fight against the pull.
Next, block the laser again with the metal box, and thanks to the purple ball's position, you don't have to worry about overshooting.
Ideally, I would've liked to have gotten that gem in just one pass, but that's okay. I didn't get hurt, and it's not like the time limit is strict on this level.
Whatever. It's okay, as Daria can tank enemy collisions quite well.
Well done there. Next, the one to the lower-left. This one could be tricky...
But, just like with those other magnets, these give you unlimited mana while you're in their grip as well.
!ush!
And then there's 7-3, which I'll be playing next. So, let's check out those electromagnetic fields with Trumpet Mira!
Okay, I want to handle this guy from below, really carefully...
Hello, and welcome back to Miracle Fly! Okay, here are the voting results this time: 1 vote for 7-2. Yep, that's it.
Gotcha! Okay, now for the final enemy. I can use the lasers as defensive cover if I'm careful.
Woo, that went perfectly!
And, done!
D'oh. I hate it when I accidentally click outside the window and cause the game to pause.
WAH! NOOO!!!
So, this level features magnets too, but they're slightly different than in the previous level. These can grab you and affect your movement from any direction, not just preset directions.
C-C-C-C-COMBO BREAKER!!! (8 kills, 18,000 points)
Fighting snipers while around these magnets can be a thing. You can use the magnets themselves as shields, but it can be quite tricky to maneuver and line up your shots properly without screwing up.
Your voting options are: 7-4 (Serial Trouble), 7-7 (Black Out), 7-A (Barophobia), and 9-B (Magma Tower). And, don't forget there's also all those costumes you can vote for as well!
Wow, I definitely got lucky with my shots there, taking out that sniper quickly before he could snipe me while I was flailing about.
Hmm... The magnets that pull you downward don't seem to be quite as strong as the others, and make you fall downward only slightly faster than the level's normal low gravity does.

BTW, the first time I played this level, I didn't know about the purple ball at all, but I found a way to get this gem with the help of Mira's splash damage shots. Perhaps I'll make a video showing how I did that later.
One reason being, I've got a combo going here.
Alright, now here's the part that I expect to take hits on-- the red "!" challenge. You get 28 seconds to defeat 4 snipers, but the magnets make this a pain. I hope I'll survive...
Okay, now with all those guys cleared out, fly up here, move the green block to the right, and then click on this triangle block 6 times, so that the blue gate is opened, and the C node is active.
You can use this triangle block here as a shield to block this guy's shots.
Excellent. Between the red "!" dot, the laser walls, and the sniper, it's likely you'll get hit by something, and even I sometimes get hit there, but not this time!
Wow, I think I got lucky there. Okay, next will be the one below that.
GAH!!! I told you that magnet down there was bad news! It even managed to throw off my groove up here!

Now, I could just exit the level right now if I wanted to, but I'm not gonna do that without the third gem, so let's head left, and be very careful of the moving magnets, as it's really easy to lose control around them.
Ack! It can be quite a bit trickier to maneuver with these magnets, though...
Oops. Well, I can hit the blue gate switch to proceed with the level here, but I really want to circle around again and kill that guy.
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Now, see that little red "!" dot there? If you shoot it or crash into it, it explodes, so it's a good idea to detonate it from afar, like this.

Now, with the B gate open, the level can be continued, and with the yellow gate open, we can proceed down this way towards gem #2. (BTW, I believe the purple ball initially started off hidden in the blocks above the yellow gate.)
Oh, and magnets have another property. So, let's waste some mana by spraying arrows all over the place here...
Now, I can sorta cheese this one by firing in between the C block and the left triangle block, and he can't successfully return fire the same way, so I'm completely safe from him by doing this.
Yep! I caused a ball way up above to fall down to there. Now, let's go back and do some left rotations.
Very good. Next, I think I'll take on the sniper to the left. I'll try to bait him to shoot over my head.
Okay, this next part is kinda tricky to get through without getting hurt.

Oohhhh, and I think there are exactly enough coins here to put me at a value that I can get the 3-star bonus with! Just gotta make sure I pick up every coin, and hit the goal when the timer's ones digit is 0...
Huzzah! I nailed it! Wow, this level went so well for me here!
Alright, that unlocked... 7-7, surprisingly. So, guys, make sure to vote this time!
And another reason being...
...Did I seriously just do that? Well, no matter, as my combo was gonna be ended by the purple button above anyway.
And, this is really great, since I've got a combo going, and there's several enemies up ahead that I can add to this combo. I'd like to combo them all together, if at all possible.

...Oy! Well, I only took one hit, so I did fare better than I expected, and I can still survive one more hit if I need to. (I kinda wish this level had a health potion in it, but those are quite rare at this point in the game.)
But, Mira and I think Daria can hit the sniper from here. (Irvette would need to get closer, within its firing range.)
And, of course, the movable metal boxes are also magnetic, and can be pulled by the magnets.
Perfect. You want the purple ball resting in that corner, just like that.
Okay, the 5th hit destroyed that one.
Rotating to the left will get the purple door to swing so you can get through, and eventually cause the purple ball to roll onto the yellow gate switch. But, even after that, rotate left a bit more.
Man, that must be a tough sniper, since it survived 4 of Mira's shots. Most regular enemies are defeated in 4 shots or fewer from Mira.
